    "updated_at": "2015-10-29T18:05:03Z",
    "body": "Was this fixed? I'm having the same issue on Windows 7 running Electron 0.32.2 as well as Electron 0.34.1. I've tried two different code examples: \n\n  `app.on('will-quit', function()\n  {\n    if (process.platform != 'darwin')\n      app.quit();\n  });`\n\nas well as \n\n`app.on('window-all-closed', function()\n{\n    if (process.platform != 'darwin')\n      app.quit();\n  });`\n\nI have two open processes, close the window and I'm stuck with one. Thanks for your time!\n\n-Alec\n"
